deck_excerpt: Shaddoll Kashtira Tearlaments / YCS Dortmund Top 32
deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Deck

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Flaminio Rossi

Tournament: YCS Dortmund - October 1st 2023

Placement: Top 32

Goat Format had stuff similar to this so I guess I just transfered it to Edison Format. Some variations of this do exist, but they're more inclinded to use stall burn instead, which is lame and takes the aggro out of this deck to just sit on advantage and burn. This variation just wants to stack as much damage as humanly possible through a great combination of effects, burn, and punching power.

Unlike some versions we can't really abuse stuff like Panda + Ojama Trio due to many meta decks relying on potentially using the Ojama tokens for big special summons, so no Panda and one Ojama copy, mostly for later game or to brick up the field. The base of the deck is instead around Koala due to doing stupid amounts of damage and being a pretty great wall by his lonesome, of which it's been really useful in doing so in testing as a reliable set; it's kinda funny how much people sleep on the card despite it having some really great utility. It can be used for:

1. Set into big burn (generally 1/2k depending on hand size and if they can even beat over it with whatever is attacking)

2. Play as wall 

3. As a low-threat poker with a chainable Moon

4. As a Rescue Cat target for potential level 6 Synchro

etc

Spy's another thing borrowed from Goat Format and it's just as good if not better here given Decendent is around for easy and solid removal. Despite the weird synergy in this kind of deck it's actually worked really well in mixing things up and getting monsters on the field as soon as possible. Guard is a good alternative and his bouncing is remarkably potent on a lot of boss monsters in the format.

For the aggro it comes mostly from the mix of big statlines from Gorilla/Cyber/Gorz and co with the boost from Rescue Cat and Nimble/Ryko or Koala being able to keep the monster flow going. The Airbellum copies are of course great as beaters/tuners to boot. 

Spells are kept to generally basic stuff, mostly ways to destroy or run through deck faster. Side deck includes Necrovalley and Commandment in case it's needed to either get the Gravekeepers a boost and/or block graveyard heavy combos.

Traps are, again, generally basic, mostly designed around being things that you can either chain around or for general battle protection. Obviously this is where the big damage comes from and it generally causes the most issues for a first game. 

Side deck is essential because most decks tend to run Royal Decree as a anti-trap option, which can be a fair issue for this kind of deck. At that point I usually change things up by adding splashers in Giant Rat and Injection Lily as a nasty combo that is hard to predict accurately and settling more for general damage instead while they're busy trying to play around the burn issue. Starlight Road was a considered option, but seeing as you aren't really sitting on backrow you want to protect, I couldn't really see it as something to use here, through it can definitely be useful if this is made slower with more field control and the like.

Hello hello! I was bored, and wanted to do a playthrough by going through the OCG sets, making an updated Common Charity deck as we go!

The very first set is nothing too special, literal caveman Yu-Gi-Oh at its finest. There really isnt a strategy, just summon some guys (preferably the 1200 guys since they are the biggest you're getting) and hit as hard as possible. Sparks is for that oh so crucial burn damage, and Red Medicine is to help heal up to 1500 LP, which in a grindier state like this might actually help out a bit!

Opening 30 packs of Booster 1, I was hoping we'd get some better monsters for the deck, and we honestly did. Although there weren't any monters stronger than 1200, what we did get helped to even out the decks power level, allowing us to remove all the 700 attackers that I needed to fill out the deck with mostly 900 ATK monsters that, although still not stronger, at least are better stat wise.

The only other "big" change is adding in Raimei, just for a little more burn damage. Although we didn't get anything ground breaking, it at least helped to increase the general average power of our deck! (Had to list it under Fun/Casual since Raimei is a Rare in TCG but is a Common in this set soooo-)

deck_excerpt: generaider, albaz, world gears, demiurgy, kaiju, ygoprodeck.com, non-meta deck, fun deck, local, fun, big sweety monster, boss monster,
deck_description:
Generaider is a deck that aim at controlling the field and dish out powerful blow once everything is cleared.

Vala, Seidhr of the Generaider Bosses and Loptr, Shadow of the Generaider Bosses are two of the most importants cards in the deck and are required to have any form of consistency. Generaider Boss Stage is the bread and butter of the deck, nothing can be achieve without having it on board, Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light and Generaider Boss Quest are here to bring it to the field.

Your ideal setup with this decklist would be to summon Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows during your first turn with your field spell and a trap (ideally, Generaider Boss Room because it will protect your activated effect from being negated). Then, as soon as your opponent draw a card in its draw phase, you will be able to summon Harr, Generaider Boss of Storms to the field (He is a powerful Omni-Negate that can also force your opponent to send a monster from his field or hand to the graveyard).

Generaider will need tributing (they either ask for Generaider monster or for monster that have the same type as them) to activate most of their disruptive effect, Harr, Generaider Boss of Storms and Utgarda, Generaider Boss of Delusion will need 2, Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows will need to tribute herself. Luckily, that's where our field spell comes in action again. If you summon a Generaider monster during your opponent turn, you will be able to fill your empty main monster zone with Generaider Token.

Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows has a powerful effect, it can tribute itself to summon another Xyz Generaider monster (Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity) and then it let you attach as much card from any field or graveyard to it as Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows had material. 

Considering Generaider monsters are mostly level 9 monster, World Legacy Monstrosity is a must as it allow you to summon powerful Xyz (Infinitrack Earth Slicer) or Link monster (World Gears of Theurlogical Demiurgy) fast (and also one good may to summon Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light if you don't have it in hand).

As much as this deck loves to special summon their big bad monster, it's also a deck that loves to control and can play through Summon Limit, that's why I play it in the main deck. You can still use both effect of your field spell under Summon Limit which is more than enough once you are setup. This decklist can be improve with more handtrap or disruptive card (such as There Can Be Only One (be careful with this one, even if all Generaider have different type, all your token are fairy), Infinite Impermanence, Effect Veiler,...). 
It is important to note that, as it is a deck with, almost only, level 9 monster, Generaider can brick. Your oppening hand could be 5 monster that can't be summoned. There should be enough tool to prevent this happening too much time but it cannot be fully prevented. It also struggle a lot playing second without more hand trap and fast board breaker. 

Albaz the Ashen is also present here, as a one of (or more if needed) because Generaider can play without their normal summon (thanks to Vala and Monstrosity), and in case of going second, being able to summon it and bring Mirrorjade the Iceblade Dragon to the table really helped me in some situation. It might be stupid to have it only at once for a first duel, it can easily be replace by something else, it's more of a "i like it card" than anything.

Generaider has been my go-to deck for a while now, the addition of Vala, Seidhr of the Generaider Bosses and Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows this year really helped make this deck way stronger than it uses to be and I've always had a blast playing it. I've tried it against some meta deck and, even if it's far from being one, Generaider will not go without a fight against them.

That's all for this deck, hope you have a blast trying it.

deck_excerpt: If you aren't playing Colorless in Dark World, why not play it in Lady of Lament?
deck_description:
Maze of Millennia is coming out at the start of 2024, bringing us great cards like Transaction Rollback and meh cards like Colorless, Chaos King of Dark World. Let's put them into a Deck. But first, a question: "What monster is a Level 3 DARK Fiend whose combined ATK and DEF equal 2000 and can be used as a Fusion Material substitute?" That's right, it's Versago the Destroyer. Not only can it substitute itself for a named monster for a Fusion Summon, it is also a Level 3 DARK Fiend monster which allows you to get it from Deck off of Ties of the Brethren in your Lady of Lament Deck, or you can target it on field with Ties to get your Lady of Laments out of the Deck. And guess what card is a Normal Trap? That's right, it's Necro Fusion. You can set it off of Lilith because it's a Normal Trap and you can use it alongside Versago to bring out Fusion Monsters such as Colorless, Fusion Grapha, and Granguignol on your opponent's turn to make full use of their effects to their maximum potential.

Main Deck monsters: 3 Lord of the Heavenly Prison. You can reveal this card in your hand to give all of your set cards destruction protection. Then, if a set Spell/Trap is activated, you can summon it from hand, and if it was already revealed, you can set a Spell/Trap from Deck. Protection is always great, and being able to easily bring out a very large body with the additional effect of being able to set any Spell/Trap from Deck is incredible. 3 Lady Labrynth of the Silver Castle. She can be Summoned from hand the turn a Normal Trap was activated, and while you control a Set card, she cannot be destroyed or targeted by your opponent's card effects. Also, if you activate a Normal Trap, you can set a Normal Trap with a different name from Deck. Again, this is a very easily summonable, large body with the added effect of setting a Normal Trap directly from your Deck. 2 Versago the Destroyer. It is a Level 3 DARK Fiend who can substitute itself for a Fusion Material listed on a Fusion Monster for a Fusion Summon. To reiterate, Versago is a Level 3 DARK Fiend, making it a target for Ties on the field and a target in Deck to Summon off of Ties. And with it being able to substitue itself for any monster listed on a Fusion Monster for a Fusion Summon, you can use it in tandem with Necro Fusion in order to get out Fusion Monsters with a handful of useful effects on your opponent's turn that all vary in what they do. I would only play 1 because playing more copies does increase the chances of you drawing it, which is really not optimal. But since Necro Fusion is not once per turn and since it banishes monsters from the GY face-down as Fusion Material, I feel like playing 2 is more than enough for our purposes. 2 Tour Guide From the Underworld which on Normal Summon, Special Summons a Level 3 Fiend from hand or Deck with its effects negated. This gives you easy Rank 3 access to make something like D/D/D Stone King Darius to go into either Zeus or D/D/D Deviser King Deus Machinex. In addition to that, it can also get out necessary Level 3 Fiends out of your Deck, being Versago or our next card. Doomdog Octhros, which we only play 1 of. When it is sent from field to GY, it is a mandatory effect to add a Level 8 Fiend monster from Deck to hand. It is really good to get off of Ties of the Brethren in order to be Tributed by Lilith. Lilith then sets a Normal Trap from Deck while Doomdog gets to search you Lady Labrynth from Deck. 3 Lilith Lady of Lament who is a Quick Effect to Tribute a DARK monster to reveal 3 Normal Traps in your Deck and have your opponent randomly choose 1 for you to set. This is a great way of accessing Traps, on your turn to prepare for your opponent's turn, or on your opponent's turn for follow-up. 3 Alice, Lady of Lament who can Summon a Lady of Lament from GY on Normal Summon and she can also banish a Trap from hand or GY to Summon herself from hand. Then, if she is tributed, she can search a Fiend from Deck whose ATK/DEF total to 2000. Usually, you are going to be searching Lilith for next turn, but you can also search for Versago in case you want it in rotation for next turn. 

For Spell/Traps: 3 Ties of the Brethren. This targets a Level 4 or lower monster on field and Special Summons 2 monsters with the same Level, Type, and Attribute from your Deck with different names. This is a crucial card in Lady of Lament as it gets all of the necessary monsters on field, while also providing Tribute fodder for Lilith for her to set Normal Traps from Deck. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 2 Necro Fusion. This is a Normal Trap that Fusion Summons a Fusion Monster from Extra Deck by banishing Fusion Materials from GY face-down. Since this card is a Normal Trap, it is easily searchable by Lilith, and you could optionally play a copy of Trap Trick if you really wanted to, in order to access it even more often. And of course, with Versago being easily integratable into the Lady of Lament strategy, you can use it to substitue a named Fusion Material such as Reign-Beaux, Overlord of Dark World for Colorless, Grapha, Dragon Lord of Dark World for Fusion Grapha, and Blazing Cartesia, the Virtuous for Granguignol. 3 Archfiend's Ghastly Glitch which targets a card on field if you control a Fiend and destroys it, and then it allows you the option to send a Fiend from Deck to GY. First of all, this card is not once per turn, which means that having multiple copies set or in your starting hand does not dampen any of your potential plays on your opponent's turn. Second, it pops any card on field which is very good for targeting monsters and backrow. Third, it gives you the option of sending a Fiend from Deck to GY afterwards. You can send Versago in the situation where you did not get him into rotation turn 1 in order for your Necro Fusion to be live and have the ability to Summon your Fusions with named material. It also gives you the option to activate multiple Necro Fusions if you opened more than 1. Necro Fusion banishes materials from GY face-down, so being able to put more material in grave is really good. 3 Infinite Impermanence. 3 Destructive Daruma Karma Cannon which changes as many monsters on the field to face-down Defense Position and sends all remaining face-up monsters to GY. This is very good against many Link strategies such as Unchained because you need face-up monsters to Link Summon, and it gives you a way to clear Links with a non-destruction-based effect. 3 Transaction Rollback. This allows you to pay half your Life Points to copy the effect of a Normal Trap in your opponent's GY. However, you can also banish it from your GY and pay half your Life Points to copy the effect of a Normal Trap in your GY. This means you can copy Ghastly Glitch for another pop, Imperm for a monster negate, Karma Cannon to deal with your opponent's board, or even Necro Fusion for another Fusion Summon. And finally, 3 Solemn Judgment for protection purposes.

For the Extra Deck: 1 Colorless, Chaos King of Dark World. It requires Reign-Beaux, Overlord of Dark World and 2 or more Fiend monsters. This is easily achievable in Lady of Lament with the Deck being able to put Versago into rotation to substitute from Reign-Beaux and the Lilith being able to Tribute off the Fiends you Summoned from Ties of the Brethren in order to put Fusion Material in the GY for Necro Fusion to Summon out Colorless. On Fusion Summon, Colorless destroys all cards your opponent controls. This is especially nice with you Summoning on your opponent's turn with Necro Fusion. It also gains 1000 ATK/DEF equal to the number of Fusion Materials used to Summon it, but that isn't that relevant unless we take into account the Virus Traps of which we are siding 1 Eradicator Epidemic Virus. Also, it can Quick Effect discard a card and make a face-up card you control untargetable by your opponent's effects for the turn. It isn't much of an effect, especially since our Deck mostly has set Traps on field and Lilith Tributes off most of your monsters eitherway, so the best target you have for Colorless is itself, which still isn't much. 1 Grapha, Dragon Overlord of Dark World. This requires Grapha, Dragon Lord of Dark World and a DARK monster for Fusion Material, but again, this is achievable with Versago. If your opponent activates a monster effect or a Normal Spell/Trap, it can change the effect to "your opponent discards 1 card" which effectively nullifies or negates that effect depending on how you look at it. This is very helpful for stopping board breaker cards like Lightning Storm, Harpie's Feather Duster, and Evenly Matched which are bad match-ups for your Deck depending on how you open. 1 Predaplant Triphyoverutum which can negate a Special Summon from the Extra Deck and destroy those monsters, and it can Special Summon itself back grom GY if your opponent controls a monster with a Predator Counter. This is in here as a Super Poly target as it does require 3 DARK monsters on field as Fusion Material. 1 Predaplant Dragostapelia which requires a Fusion Monster and a DARK monster for Fusion Material and can Quick Effect place a Predator Counter on a face-up monster your opponent controls and it negates all activated monster effects of monsters your opponent controls with a Predator Counter. 1 Despian Proskenion which can be Summoned off of Granguignol's effect. It can Quick Effect target a Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, or Link in your opponent's GY and either banish it or summon it to yoru field. And if it destroys a mosnter by battle, it can inflict damage to your opponent equal to the destroyed monster's ATK or DEF, whichever is higher. 1 Granguignol the Dusk Dragon which requires Blazing Cartesia, the Virtuous and a LIGHT or DARK monster which is very achievable, again, due to Versago. If it's Fusion Summoned, it can dump a Level 6 or higher LIGHT or DARK monster from your Deck or Extra Deck. The only realistic target we have for this effect that actually does something is Garura for a draw, but you can play other options like Darkest Diabolos, Lord of the Lair if you really wanted. And when your opponent Special Summons a monster by an activated monster effect, you can banish Granguignol from field or GY to summon a Despia from Extra Deck or a Dogmatika from Deck. Our only target is Proskenion, which is still probably the best thing you could do. 1 Starving Venom Fusion Dragon, 1 Garura, Wings of Resonant Life, and 1 Mudragon of the Swamp for Super Poly targets. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder along with 1 Downerd Magician to play alongside your 1 D/D/D Stone King Darius and 1 Number 49: Fortune Tune for Zeus plays. 1 D/D/D Deviser King Deus Machinex to Rank-up Darius into for interruption if you draw Tour Guide and have no real other plays. 1 Salamangreat Almiraj just to be able to Link off Doomdog to search Lady Labrynth.

Side Deck: 3 Kashtira Fenrir and 1 Dinowrestler Pankratops as free Summons from hand that you can use to boardclear. 3 Super Polymerization for more board clears, and it fits the whole Fusion aspect of the Deck well. 2 Dimensional Barrier. 2 Terrors of the Overroot. 1 Eradicator Epidemic Virus, and 3 Evenly Matched.

"Orcust" is an archetype of DARK Machine monsters that debuted in Soul Fusion. They are related to the "World Legacy" archetype. The name Orcust may be a portmanteau of "orchestra" and "locust", referring to their endless numbers in the archetype's lore; it may also be a reference to Orcus. "Horus" is an archetype first introduced in Soul of the Duelist, and that received its first support in Age of Overlord. It's primally consisted of two groups: the "Horus the Black Flame Dragon" sub-archetype and monsters related to it, and a set of Level 8 monsters that support "King's Sarcophagus". deck_name: Lady of Lament ft. RDA & Friends
deck_excerpt: You could say that the Crimson King Structure Deck brings some goodies to Lady of Lament
deck_description:
The Crimson King Structure Deck gives great support to Red Dragon Archfiend. But with some of that support being given out to Resonators and "Archfiends" and/or Fiends in general (if you can categorize them like that), it gives some nice cards that work well with another Fiend strategy, that being Lady of Lament. The cards from that debut in the Structure Deck which are featured here include Bone Archfiend, Vision Resonator, Crimson Gaia, and Fiendish Golem, but you can also include Scarred Dragon Archfiend as well. This isn't so much of a Red Dragon Archfiend Deck as it is more of a Lady of Lament Deck making use of some of the new Red Dragon Archfiend support while still retaining some ability to go into Red Dragon Archfiend and associated Synchros to some degree. There are some benefits to playing this Deck, but they don't make the Deck any much more of a consideration over your average Lady of Lament Deck. This is just an idea I was tinkering with and the product was pretty good to a degree. 

For the Main Deck monsters: 3 Lord of the Heavenly Prison which can reveal itself in hand to give all of your Set cards destruction protection while it is revealed. And if you activate a Set Spell/Trap, you can Special Summon it from hand, and if it was already revealed in hand when you do so, you can set a Spell/Trap from Deck. Lord gives a lot of utility, being protecting your Set Spell/Traps from destruction while also being an easily summonable, large body that can also get you any Spell/Trap directly from Deck. 3 Bone Archfiend which can send a card from hand or field to GY in order to Summon it from hand or GY which then locks you into DARK Dragon Synchro Monsters from the Extra Deck. It being this easy to Summon plays extremely well with its next effect. On field, you can target a monster you control with a Level and send a Fiend Tuner from hand or Deck to GY to increase or decrease that monster's Level by 1. This means that you can turn this Level 4 DARK Fiend monster into a Level 3 DARK Fiend monster on field. This means that you now have a target on field for Ties of the Brethren to get your Lady of Lament monsters out from the Deck. And what's even better is that it doesn't even need your Normal Summon. Sure, it locks you into Dark Dragon Synchros out of the Extra Deck for the rest of the turn, but you can just Normal Summon like a Tour Guide right before that, go into D/D/D Stone King Darius and rank him up into D/D/D Deviser King Deus Machinex. And it gets even better when you realize that you can send Vision Resonator from Deck with it. We are playing 2 Vision Resonator. You can make the argument to play only 1 as you can add it back with Crimson Gaia, but that is ONLY IF you want to add it back with Crimson Gaia. Crimson Gaia adds any card that lists RDA from Deck or GY which means you can search other cards that are better in the moment. But back to Vision Resonator, if you control a Level 5 or higher DARK monster, you can Special Summon it from hand, and if it is sent to GY, you can add a Spell/Trap that mentions RDA from Deck. Our only options are Crimson Gaia and Fiendish Golem, but those are good enough in the context of this Deck and I will explain why once we get to the Spell/Traps of the Deck. However, since Vision Resonator is also a Tuner, it is our way to access Red Dragon Archfiend and its other Synchros in the Extra Deck. It and a Level 4 Bone Archfiend get you to Red Rising Dragon which brings back Vision Resonator to go into a Level 8 like Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend for functionally a boardwipe. Or since we are siding Bystials, Vision Resonator, who is a 2, Synched with a Level 6 Bystial, immediately gets you to a Level 8 RDA Synchro for the same purposes. Then, we are playing 1 Sangan which searches a monster with 1500 or less ATK when sent from field. Sangan can be Tributed off of Lilith or sent from field for Bone Archfiend, but the most important part about it is that it can search a monster for follow-up. 3 Lilith, Lady of Lament which is a Quick Effect to Tribute a DARK monster to reveal 3 Normal Traps in Deck and have your opponent randomly choose 1 for you to Set to your field. This is a great way to access Traps, especially since you are also playing monsters who benefit off of either being Tributed, sent from field to GY, or sent to GY in general. Then, we are playing 3 Alice, Lady of Lament who Special Summons a Lady of Lament from GY on Normal Summon which can include itself. This means that if you send a Lady of Lament from hand to Special Summon Bone Archfiend, you can Normal Summon Alice to get it back, and if it happens to be Lilith, it's as if you activated Ties of the Brethren, but you didn't and still got everything that you needed on field either way which is really nice. You can also banish a Trap from hand or GY to Special Alice from hand, and if it is Tributed, you can add a Fiend monster from Deck to hand whose combined ATK and DEF equal to 2000. Your only option in this Deck is Lilith, but simply just having a Lilith for next turn is already pretty good. Also, you can search another Alice for follow-up next turn with Sangan if you have the option to. And finally, 2 Tour Guide From the Underworld which Special Summons a Level 3 Fiend from hand or Deck on Normal Summon. This card is basically a 1-card Rank 3 which translates into a Machinex if you decide to go for Darius. And to reiterate, you can Normal Summon Tour Guide and go into an Xyz before you Special Summon Bone Archfiend which functionally gives you more interruption in Machinex while also having a Level 3 DARK Fiend on field as a target for Ties. 

For Spell/Traps: 3 Ties of the Brethren which targets a Level 4 or lower monster on field and Special Summons 2 monsters from Deck with different names that have the same Level, Type, and Attribute as the targeted monster. This gives you access to all of your Lady of Lament monsters, giving you Lilith access with Tribute fodder for her effect as well. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Crimson Gaia. It is a Continuous Spell that can add an RDA or a card that mentions it from Deck or GY to hand each turn. This means that it can add back Vision Resonator to possibly go into a Synchro play or search/add back Fiendish Golem to recur Trap options for removal as it does mention RDA. Crimson Gaia also allows you to change all monsters your opponent controls to face-down Defense when an RDA declares an attack, and if a monster(s) is destroyed by battle or card effect on field, it can Special Summon an RDA from GY. These effects are really good. You wouldn't be using the second effect of Crimson Gaia that much in this Deck specifically, but being able to Summon back an RDA from GY pretty constently is really powerful, considering that we can bring back Scarlight for board clears almost every turn, in case it is outed the first time around. 3 Infinite Impermanence. 3 Archfiend's Ghastly Glitch which allows you to target and destroy a card on field if you control a Fiend monster, and afterwards, it allows you to send a Fiend from Deck to GY. Being able to destroy any card on field with a Trap that is not once per turn is really good, especially with the added option of sending a Fiend from Deck. This means that you can send an additional copy of Vision Resonator to possibly search another Fiendish Golem if you already did not get all copies of it out of the Deck or Crimson Gaia if you did not already search it. 1 Trap Trick. 2 Transaction Rollback which allows you to pay half your Life Points to copy the effect of a Normal Trap in your opponent's GY, but you can also banish it from your GY and pay half your Life Points to copy the effect of a Normal Trap in your GY. What's even better is the fact that you can send it from hand to Summon Bone Archfiend, giving you access to its grave effect, which is arguably better than its effect when activated on field. 2 Dimensional Barrier. 2 Fiendish Golem. This card allows you to target a monster with 2000 or more ATK and banish until the End Phase of the next turn, then, if you controlled an RDA or a Synchro that mentions it when you activated this card, you can set a Fiendish Chain from Deck or GY. It's not the most impressive card, I will admit. You are not getting rid of a monster for good, and you are limited to only using it on monsters with 2000 or more ATK which is why I am comfortable playing it at 2 and not at 3. Besides, you can add it back from GY with Crimson Gaia eitherway. And if you really wanted to be cute, you could play 1 Fiendish Chain, but I feel it isn't necessary with the fact that we are already playing 3 Infinite Impermanence with Transaction Rollback in this Deck. Also, we are basically almost never going to be Summoning RDA or an associated Synchro monster in our regular combo for this Deck. If anything, the RDA Synchros that we are playing in this Deck are more for turn 3 and beyond in the case of going first to have a way of reducing your opponent's Life Points to 0 and/or clearing their board. Or for turn 2 in the case of going second to clear threats on your opponent's board. And finally, 3 Torrential Tribute.

For the Extra Deck: 1 Garura, Wings of Resonant Life and 1 Elder Entity N'tss to send off of Ultimate Slayer. Garura gives you a draw while N'tss pops a card on field. 1 Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend. It's name becomes Red Dragon Archfiend while on field or in GY which means that you can bring it back with Crimson Gaia which is really nice. Also, as a soft once per turn, you can destroy as many Special Summoned Effect Monsters on field with ATK less than or equal to this card's and inflict 500 to your opponent for each monster destroyed. The reason why I mentioned the soft once per turn is because, in the case of your opponent negating and destroying the activated effect of Scarlight, Crimson Gaia can just bring it back and you can try it again. Scarlight gives you a really nice way of dealing with monster threats on your opponent's board on a follow-up turn or going second. 1 Scarred Dragon Archfiend and 1 Red Dragon Archfiend. Scarred's name becomes Red Dragon Archfiend on field or GY which, again, means that Crimson Gaia can bring it back from GY. If it is sent from the Monster Zone to the GY, you can Special Summon the 1 Red Dragon Archfiend that we are also playing in our Extra Deck (and this is treated as a Synchro Summon), and then, if it was used as Synchro Material fro a DARK Dragon Synchro Monster, you can destroy all Attack Position monsters your opponent controls. Okay, so here is the deal. We are playing Scarred Dragon Archfiend to have a large body that we can Summon from the Extra Deck that can float into another large body. HOWEVER, please remember that Red Dragon Archfiend will destroy all monsters you control that did not declare an attack this turn during the End Phase. Even if it can destroy all Defense Position monsters your opponent controls after damage calc of a battle in which it attacked a Defense Position monster, you really have to be careful about doing things like Summoning monsters during Main Phase 2 or having small monstes on your field that were able to get over your opponent's monsters or attack your opponent directly during the Battle Phase because RDA will just blow all of them up. This is just a reminder to be careful of when you are using Scarred Dragon Archfiend to Summon Red Dragon Archfiend from your Extra Deck. If you choose to do so, you may end up destroying your board instead. 1 Red Rising Dragon which is a Level 6 Synchro that can be made with Vision Resonator and Bone Archfiend. When it is Synchro Summoned, it can summon back a Resonator from GY, that being Vision Resonator, giving you access to a Level 8 Synchro, being an RDA Synchro of your choice in this Deck. 1 Golden Cloud Beast - Malong which returns a face-up card your opponent controls to the hand when sent to GY, making it a good send off of Ultimate Slayer. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 1 D/D/D Deviser King Deus Machinex which can be ranked up into with Darius and it can attach a Monster Card your opponent controls that activated its effect to itself once per chain by detaching 2 materials, and if you Summon it with Darius, you usually get 2 activations of Machinex. 1 Downerd Magician to give Zeus more material. 1 D/D/D Stone King Darius which can make itself indestructible in a battle and destroy your opponent's monster instead, which makes it a good choice to go into Zeus with, but it can also rank-up into Machinex of course. 1 Number 49: Fortune Tune for the same reason to make Zeus. 1 Unchained Soul Lord of Yama which is a Link target for Ultimate Slayer as it can banish tiself when a card you control is destroyed by battle or card effect to Summon a Fiend from hand or GY. And finally, 1 Salamangreat Almiraj.

Side Deck: 1 Bystial Magnamhut, 2 Bystial Druiswurm, and 1 Bystial Baldrake. I would be playing things like Kashtira Fenrir and Pankratops in this slot, but in order to go with the whole Red Dragon Archfiend theme of the Deck, I decided to put the Bystials here in order to give you an easy Level 6 body to Summon from hand with that can be Synched with Vision Resonator to go into an RDA Synchro. But even so, the Bystials on their own are pretty good as they can remove DARK or LIGHT monsters from your opponent's GY. During the End Phase that Magnamhut was Special Summoned, it can add a Dragon from Deck or Gy to hand. Druiswurm sends a Special Summoned monster your opponent controls to GY if it is sent from field to GY, which is very easy to do in this Deck as you can just Tribute it with Lilith's effect. And Baldrake can Tribute another LIGHT or DARK when your opponent Special Summons a Ritual, Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, and/or Link to banish 1 of those monsters, and it Tributing can trigger Alice's effect to add off of being Tributed. 3 Ultimate Slayer. 2 Lightning Storm. 3 Evenly Matched. And 3 Solemn Judgment.

deck_excerpt: Just a deck I wanted to try out
deck_description: The "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" deck revolves around harnessing the raw power of the iconic Dragon and its related monsters. In the early game, you'll focus on using cards like "The Melody of Awakening Dragon" to search out your "Blue-Eyes" and its alternative counterpart. Simultaneously, "Trade-In" and "Dragon Shrine" help establish your graveyard and cycle through your deck. "Sage with Eyes of Blue" serves a dual purpose: searching for key tuners and initiating combos. As you transition to the mid-game, you'll aim to establish a dominant board presence with Synchro monsters like "Blue-Eyes Spirit Dragon" and Xyz monsters such as "Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy". These monsters not only offer offensive capabilities but also disrupt and negate your opponent's strategies. "Return of the Dragon Lords" acts as a linchpin, reviving your fallen Dragons while shielding them from harm. As matches progress, rely on your Extra Deck for adaptability, and don't forget to strategically side in counters after the first game to tackle specific opponent threats. Mastery of this deck comes from maximizing the synergy between your powerful Dragons and the suite of support cards tailored to elevate their strengths.

deck_excerpt: That's a nice time you have there, be a shame if someone stole it.
deck_description:
Ok I need to talk about the Time Thief monsters, and how weird they are. Some of them are spectacular, like Time Thief Winder and Time Thief Regulator. BUT, you also have cards that are useless like Time Thief Chronocorder. What are you supposed to do with that? Also Time Thief Temporwhal. At a glance, it seems like it would work well with Time Thief Adjuster, but Adjuster  can only use on effect per turn, so it doesn't work. The extra deck monsters are all great though. Time Thief Redoer needs no introduction, and carries this deck on its back. Time Thief Double Barrel is just a win-more card. If you're in a position where you can resolve the graveyard effect of Time Thief Startup onto Time Thief Double Barrel, you'd win anyway. Time Thief Perpetua is also a spectacular card, letting you add more traps to Time Thief Redoer.

So, how do you actually play Time Thieves? When going first, you just have to bring out Regulator. Then, you can summon Winder and Adjuster, search Flyback or Retrograde if your starting hand already had Flyback, mill Bezel Ship, go into Redoer, then use Bezel Ships effect to send Winder and summon itself. Then at the start of the next turn, use Flyback to attach another Flyback to Redoer. This gets you a pretty good interruption with Redoers trap effect.

Of course, this isn't the only way to do this. If you open Shade Brigandine, you can use Regulator to go into Winder and Bezel Ship, then use Shade Brigandine and Winder to go into Redoer. Theres no set pattern, but all the stuff above is a good starting point. But, of course, the worst may end up occuring...

What if you do not have Regulator in your starting hand? Firstly, if you have Small World and another Time Thief, you can use it, banish Goblindbergh from the deck, and search Regulator. But if you're not that lucky, pray the cards you have in hand somehow let you go into Redoer. 

If you manage to survive turn two, on turn three you want to try and go into Perpetua, or if you already have Startups graveyard effect set up, then you want to consider going into Double Barrel. Keep in mind that even if you have it set up, it may sometimes be better to go into Perpetua. 

So, what about going second?

Uhh... well you see, you can... uhh... I mean you have Ash Blossom. Thats... something. I guess.

Please keep in mind that I suck at yu-gi-oh. If you look at this and think, "Wow, what is Chespin04124 doing? Why did they add this card/not include this other card? What are they doing???" please leave a comment and help me improve this crappy deck.

my take on a pretty intuitive combo of archetypes i've seen other people play around with. definitely in need of some tweaking, but pretty fun so far. i like Kahyoreigetsu because it can extend both of the main types of monsters and dragons are always everywhere, so the bounce effect will sometimes be live, plus the search is nice. i'm like 70% sure Super Polymerization can bring out Windwitch - Crystal Bell but i actually don't know if you have to use cards from both sides of the field or if that's just something you can do. if not, replace her with another Super Polymerization or maybe Lyna the Light Charmer, Lustrous (though that could be the nostagia talking, i just always loved the charmers, so i'm constantly looking for excuses to stick the actual decent retrains in decks).

deck_excerpt: Runick's latest and strongest "bestie" to hang out with is "Chimera," the newest fusion archetype from Duelist Nexus!
deck_description:
Runick's latest and strongest bestie to hang out with is "Chimera," the newest fusion archetype from Duelist Nexus.  

Chimera is an incredible advantage engine capable of overwhelming your opponent with so much resources, interactions and draw power - represented in a fusion deck! For example, one Mirror Swordknight is a whopping +7 in card advantage! 

Combined with Runick, another amazing advantage engine, you get an extremely competent meta strategy that will quickly outpace your opponents! Piloted correctly and skillfully, Chimera Runick will win you games vs. the top decks of the metagame!
 
This deck may be straightforward, but it rewards good decision making since boards and gamestates are determined by the pilot's skill and resource management. If you're a player who likes a resource-based control-focused grindgame, Runick Chimera is the deck for you.
 
ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING
 
As the name implied, Runick Chimera is composed of the two archetypes. The deck also has one supporting engine, the Frightfur Patchwork Engine. 

CHIMERA creates is a simple and solid gameplan in itself with it's boss monster - Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts. While it is on the field, it's name is "Chimera the Flying Mythical Beast." In the GY, Mirror Swordknight and Cornfield Coatl (sent to the GY as part of the combo) offer some targeting protection (Coatl) and monster effect negation (Swordknight). Berfomet and Gazelle nab resources from deck when summoned and used as fusion material. The deck's fusion card, Chimera Fusion, recurs itself from the GY if Chimera the Flying Mythical Beast is on the field or GY (which is always the case). Everything in this archetype grabs resources and recurs itself in this deck so you can keep fusion summoning and interrupting your opponent! When your opponent is out of resources, Chimera can wait one turn on a full board to OTK your opponent - the only Runick variant easily able to do so. 
 
RUNICK offers the main win condition of this deck by banishing your opponent's deck. It also can summon a level 2 to start off your Spright combo in the form of Runick Hugin while simultanously searching for Runick Fountain, allowing you to draw up to three cards. Runick spells also break opponent's boards fairly well when played correctly in tandem with the other archetypes. Runick offers has solid defensive, with Hugin protecting against destruction effects while Geri dissuades the opponent from attacking. The new Fusion monster from DUNE in the Runick arsenal, Sleipnir functions as both a resource generator and almost like a "Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer/Little Night) banishing an opponent's monster once per turn, which is an excellent defensive and offensive card. Chimera makes great use of the tokens it generates as additional fusion material. Sleipnir and Geri are also beasts, which coincidentally fulfills the fusion requirements for Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts. 
 
The FRIGHTFUR patchwork engine is an excellent addition that synergizes perfectly with this deck. Edge Imp Chain is also a fiend, which coincidentally fulfills the fusion requirements for Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
The strategy of Chimera Runick is to control/banish your opponent's cards until they surrender or deck-out. In certain situations, you can also enter the battle phase and begin taking apart your opponent's board with Chimera fusion monsters and the new Generaider from DUNE, Sleipnir. The ridiculous resource advantage and control options each archetype gives the duelist should win them the duel in most circumstances. 
 
The Chimera engine provides incredible advantage through just one Mirror Swordknight. It is a net +7 after playing on your own turn and your opponent's turn! After concluding the comboline this engine usually does, you'll have Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts on the field, with Mirror Swordknight on the field ready to tribute itself on your opponent's draw phase for more searches. Here is the combo:
 
1 Mirror Swordknight = Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts on field with Mirror Swordknight (monster negate), Cornfield Coatl (targeting negate + destroy), plenty of resources to follow-up for next turn, Set Chimera Fusion (Mostly to summon Guardian Chimera on Opponent's Main Phase).
 
1. Normal summon Mirror Swordknight.
2. Tribute Mirror Swordknight and summon from deck Big-Winged Berfomet.
3. Berfomet's effect activates on-summon, searching Gazelle the King of Mythical Claws and Chimera Fusion from deck.
4. Activate Chimera Fusion to fusion summon Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts using Big-Winged Berfomet + Gazelle the King of Mythical Claws.
5. CL1 Gazelle the King of Mythical Claws to add an illusion monster from deck, CL2 Big-Winged Berfomet to summon Mirror Swordknight from GY, CL3 Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts to send a random card from your opponent's hand in the endphase.
6. Recover from GY Chimera Fusion.
7. Endphase - resolve Chimera the King of Phantom Beasts effect to end a random card from your opponent's hand.
8. During Opponent's Draw Phase - Tribute Mirror Swordknight to summon Big-Winged Berfometfrom deck,searching Gazelle the King of Mythical Claws and Chimera Fusion.
9. During Opponent's Main Phase, activate Chimera Fusion to summon Guardian Chimera for more draws + pops.
 
Depending on going first or second, you can alter the combo to your liking and to access your fusion toolbox. For example, Magnum the Reliever can destroy card on the field and also recycle a fusion/polymerization for a draw.
 
With the unique control each archetype offers and the draw 3-10+ every turn, your opponent should wither away while you snowball card advantage to victory. 
 
GENERAL TIPS
  • Similarly to Sky Striker, Runick is a toolbox control resource deck. It has a high skill ceiling since it factors in a player's decision making, resource management and match-up knowledge. Practice makes perfect with the deck!
  • The best bait for interruption are your Edge Imp/Chimera cards. After they bait out Ash Blossom, negation or interruption, your draw 3 with Runick Fountain will usually out-resource your opponent!
  • The 3 Triple Tactics Thrust are not mandatory dor this deck, and budget options are equally as viable. However, TTThrust adds an incredible amount of power to Chimera Runick , searching for Terraforming to get your engine started, or boardbreakers like Triple Tactics Talent.
  • To use Chimera Fusion, make sure you have a Beast/Fiend available in your field or hand!
  • Chimera fusion during the opponent's turn to summon Guardian Chimera serves double purpose - Destroying your opponent's cards and drawing into more Runick quick-play spells. Guardian Chimera is also a really chonky wall that most monsters would have difficulty getting over, especially when Polymerization in the GY renders it untargetable!
  • For more fusion material and interruption, summon the new Runick monster Sleipnir. If the opponent adds a card from the deck to the hand, you get a free token!
  • This deck can easily make Bagooska if you're in a pinch since it has access to many level 4s.
  • The best cards to side-out are your six cards from the Frightfur package.
 

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

CONCLUDING REMARKS
 
The Runick archetype is thematically really cool, since it feels like the POV art of each Runick card feels like I'm fighting on the Yugioh battlefield and slaying monsters like the Doomslayer or Skyrim Dragonborn with my adventure party (yeah I know I'm such a nerd lmao). It is perfect for those of us who like to self-insert themselves into our duels with an over-active imagination and bring out the "RP" in Role-Playing Games! 

That's why I looooove making variants of Runick - and Runick's newest addition to it's archetype arsenal is Chimera! Chimera meshing extremely well with Runick is a definitely a treat for an oldschool Yugi-boomer like me, since it gives some of my favourite cards from the DM era (about 23 years ago!) meta relevance!

GLHF Duelists!

deck_name: Pure Lightsworn  - Edison Format Top 4 Deck
deck_excerpt: Pure Lightsworn  - Edison Format Top 4 Deck
deck_description: Pure Lightsworn  - Edison Format Top 4 Deck
Play conservatively!

Basically the whole deck is built around getting to the end-goal of a Mass Driver FTK idea that's mildly stolen from other places. You want to get two Gateway on the field + Mass Driver and have at least one Sam monster on the field already. The idea is that you basically loop the double Gateway with something like Grandmaster by consistently throwing it into the grave with Driver, getting it back with the Gateway and then summoning it back to do the loop all over again. The loop if perfect is pretty much game-ending if they have no signficant backrow removal in response. 

The awesome thing about this deck in theory is that because Gateway doesn't actually target, the usual counters to something like this don't work, making it pretty much a one and done. You play Trunade to clear backrow, you play Starlight Road to protect any backrow that does get targetted, you play also a lot of searching/+1 cards to run through your deck faster to boot. I'm not 100% with the deck yet in terms of structure and I do think it can be drastically improved, which is why it's not mentioned as a full on deck yet. I do think it's a fairly competent threat if it starts well enough off with the first few draws, so there's that at least, and Six Sam can be played pretty well conventionally to boot so the deck doesn't fall apart without the burn stip.

deck_description: do u smell it now mr krabs
Trying to fix my Blue-Eyes/Chaos Blue-Eyes deck

Amazoness is a Deck that evolved quite a lot throughout the years. Did you know that it debuted in Labyrinth of Nightmare back in 2003/2004? Certainly we can expect some interesting cards because of that fact alone. Today we analyze this Deck in all of it's Detail and explain why I play Amazoness Blowpiper even so it seems to be awful, let's start: 

Note that a Bug prevents me yet again from using card tooltips alltogether. Instead I use Big Lettering to make clear which card we talk about. 


Help me I'm lost in the Jungle!

Don't worry... or maybe you should worry since Amazoness Archer is right behind you and a one eyed Tiger is jumpin right at you! A little note at the start. 100% play Amazoness Archer since it's allowed in TCG and pretty good in dealing 1200 - 3600 effect Damage in a single Turn. As for Master Duel we play Amazoness Spy instead but enough of that and back to the topic: What does this Deck even want to do? 

Fusion summoning is the Answer and a lot to be true. That's why we play a 24 Monster 16 Spell/Traps ratio to have enough Monsters ready to be fused. From that position Amazoness has a simple OTK line with Amazoness Augusta or a more fancy way with reverse burn alias Amazoness Swords Woman. With Amazoness Archer there would even be a burn option but that's limited to TCG only. Certainly not as straightforward as War Rock for example and that's why Amazoness is actually a good Deck. 


The Call for War Commences 

Every Deck needs starters and with Amazoness Princess , Amazoness War Chief and Amazoness Spiritualist they have 9 Monsters which get things started. All of them are primarily focused on searching your Spell & Trap lineup. 

With Amazoness Call they have a Quick Play Spell which searches anything with Amazoness in it's name and with Polymerization , Fusion Substitute and Amazoness Secret Arts they have a total of 6 Fusion Spells. 

All these cards equal 18 cards which really get this Deck up to speed easily and are pretty essencial to any kind of Amazoness Deck. 


Gathering the Amazoness Tribe 

Next up we take a look at the Maindeck Monster lineup in more Detail. At first sight there seems to be a few very suspicious cards but we will get to them don't worry: 

Amazoness Queen: L6 with 2400/1800 Statline. Amazoness Monsters can't be destroyed by Battle. A simple yet effective permanent effect which includes herself. She can prepare a Amazoness Swords Woman Reverse Burn OTK or Mass Backrow Removal with Amazoness Sage if Amazoness Call is used to make a Monster able to attack all Monsters from the opponent. Furthermore there's synergy with Amazoness Empress which can search or revive this card and she is also one of the targets to enable 2 attacks for Amazoness Augusta or can be used to make a Amazoness Pet Liger King. Certainly Amazoness Queen proofes to be quite important within this strategy. 

Amazoness War Chief: L5 with 1900/0 Statline. She has 2 HOPT's (Hard once per turns). If you control no Monsters or only Amazoness Monsters you can special her from the hand. If normal or special summoned you can set a Amazoness Spell/Trap or Polymerization from the Deck. Her search is immune to Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and she's yet another target to summon Amazoness Pet Liger King easier. She does prevent your non Amazoness Monsters from attacking that turn too. She's all around useful and a very welcome addition to speed up your Deck. 

Amazoness Paladin: L4 with 1700/300 Statline. Gains 100 ATK for each Amazoness you control. She starts out with 1800 ATK and caps at 2300 ATK with her own effect. Having Amazoness Village and the 2 Pendulum friends active will make her a 3300 ATK Normal Summon. She's a easy to summon chonk which can be lethal if combined with the GY effect of Amazoness Call. Never underestimate this lady since even the almighty Blue-Eyes White Dragon will bow before her (With the right setup). 

Amazoness Swords Woman: L4 with 1500/1600 Statline. The opponent takes the Battle Damage you would've taken from Battles with this card. I'm so glad this card exists since it's an easy out for a big Chonk problem. Have Amazoness Queen or Amazoness Empress active and use the GY effect of Amazoness Call to win against massive Boards which would otherwise be impossible to get around by simply attacking into stronger Monsters. 

Amazoness Chain Master: L4 with 1500/1300 Statline. When destroyed by Battle you can pay 1500 LP to take a look at the opponents Hand and choose a Monster from there to add to your Hand. Talk about unique effects this is something very interesting. By crashing into an opponents Monster or simply setting her (And hoping for the best) you get the full knowledge of the opponents Hand and can steal a vital Monster from him too. Suddenly you can play with Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring , Nibiru, the Primal Being or Maxx "C". All that precious Handtraps will be yours and the opponent might just scoop out of anger. Since this card is old it's missing a Once per turn. If you see multiple Monsters in the opponents Hand use Amazoness Willpower and/or Amazoness Onslaught with Amazoness Golden Whip Master combined to get this effect up to 3 times in one Battle Phase. Certainly not cheap with 4500 LP paid plus Battle Damage but also pretty much an inescapable Situation for the opponent as well. 

Amazoness Trainee: L4 with 1500/1300 Statline. Monsters destroyed by Battle with her are returned to the bottom of the Deck and she gains a 200 ATK permanent increase too. Nowadays the GY is more important then ever and having a card which prevents certain Monsters from entering that place is more important then you might think. Trust me Spright Monsters are better to be far away at the bottom of the Deck. The list of applications for her is long indeed. 

Amazoness Sage: L4 with 1400/700 Statline. If she attacked and is still on the field at the end of the Damage Step target a Spell/Trap from the opponent and destroy it. Again using the GY effect of Amazoness Call to give her multiple attacks can achieve multiple Spell & Trap removal which is nice but obviously convoluted since cards like Infinite Impermanence or Called by the Grave do exist and how Backrow acts nowadays pretty much everything can be chained. Then again against Pendulum, Equip or Permanent effect based Strategies she can work wonders so she's an nice to have option just in case. 

Amazoness Tiger: L4 with 1100/1500 Statline. Only one Amazoness Tiger can be on your Field. Gains 400 ATK for each Amazoness you control and the opponent cannot attack another Amazoness Monster. He starts with 1500 ATK and caps at 3500 ATK. With Amazoness Village and the 2 Pendulums active he will have 4500 ATK as a normal summon Monster. Having that is already strong but there's even a hidden Trap you can setup with him. Imagine you control 3 - 5 very weak Amazoness Monsters to lure the opponent into the Battle Phase. He attacks but you activate Amazoness Archers to weaken the opponents Monsters and force them to attack. Now activate Amazoness Onslaught and special summon Amazoness Tiger. Suddenly the opponent is forced to attack your massive Tiger and most likely OTK himself in the process, nice. I always liked this Tiger and even so Amazoness Pet Liger and Amazoness Pet Liger King can achieve something similar it's still the most effective with the OG Tiger. 

Amazoness Blowpiper: L3 with 800/1500 Statline. During your Standby Phase target a opponents Monster and reduce it's ATK by 500 until the End Phase. And here it is the most suspicious Card in this Deck, let me explain. It may be wise to setup her during the End Phase of the opponent with Amazoness Willpower or an Amazoness Augusta summon and then use her effect on your turn or otherwise protect her with Amazoness Empress or Amazoness Augusta. 3000 ATK is a very common Statline among Boss Monsters and with her you get that down to 2500. Not only can a Amazoness Pet Liger then get over said cards it also enables a possible OTK in these Situations. If you setup Amazoness Pet Liger or Amazoness Pet Liger King, Amazoness Augusta and Amazoness Blowpiper with an active Amazoness Village on the field (Which is pretty common) and at the start of the Battle Phase he only controls his 3000 (Now 2500 ATK) Monster, thanks to blowpiper you will deal a total of 8200/8300 damage instead of 7700/7800 and achieve an OTK. Yes you could just use something like Amazoness Paladin instead but the fact you can bring down the ATK of an opponents Monster first makes it more versatile then initially visible to be able to even clear certain threats from the opponent. 

Amazoness Spy: L3 with 800/1200 Statline. Reveal one Amazoness in Hand to special her from the Hand. When destroyed by Battle you can target a Amazoness in the GY other then Amazoness Spy and return it to the Hand or Deck. Being able to special her can setup a tribute summon from the Hand or bring Amazoness Spiritualist into play easier. Being able to return a Monster to the Deck is good to be able to summon it with Amazoness Augusta from there again and returning it to the Hand for obvious reasons. She is the next best option after Amazoness Archer in the support lineup that's why she has found a place in this Strategy for OCG/Master Duel reasons. Note that only her first effect is a HOPT so the 2nd effect could be looped just like Amazoness Chain Master's effect too.

Amazoness Princess: L3 with 1200/900 Statline. Is treated as Amazoness Queen while on the field or in the GY (Giving her almost the same applications as the OG Amazoness Queen). On Normal/Special summon she searches any Amazoness Spell/Trap to the Hand. If she declares an attack you can send another card from Hand or field to the GY to special a Amazoness from the Deck in defense except Amazoness Princess. She's your Nr.1 Starter for sure with a HOPT search for any Amazoness Spell/Trap. The ridiculous part is that her 2nd effect is not a once per turn. Banish Amazoness Call so that she may attack all Monsters (Best with Amazoness Queen and Amazoness Onslaught active) and start generating advantage. First attack: Summon Amazoness War Chief to set another Amazoness Spell/Trap or Polymerization , Second Attack: Summon Amazoness Spiritualist to search Polymerization , Third Attack: Summon Amazoness Baby Tiger , Fourth Attack: Summon whatever you like and resummon Amazoness Baby Tiger. Main Phase 2 = Fusion summon an unstoppable army of Monsters. She really brings the whole Amazoness Tribe together. 

Amazoness Scouts: L2 with 500/1100 Statline. Quick Effect: Tribute her, neither player can target Amazoness Monsters you currently control with Monster effects or destroy them by card effects this turn. She's a very nice Monster to be summoned before passing your turn. She can protect a lonely Amazoness Empress or Amazoness Augusta very well which do protect all other cards and in general Amazoness Scouts becomes versatile because of the Quick Effect nature. Just beware using it during your turn since you also can't destroy/target your own Monsters then. 

Amazoness Baby Tiger: L2 with 500/500 Statline. Is treated as Amazoness Tiger while on the field or in the GY. Can be special summoned from the Hand or GY if you Normal/Special summon an Amazoness Monster (HOPT). Gains 100 ATK for each Amazoness Card in the GY. He's a great recurring fusion Material and can be used to summon Amazoness Pet Liger which needs an Amazoness Tiger as fusion Material. He also continues to grow stronger the bigger your GY grows which can make him annoying to Deal with in Duels which take several turns. 

Amazoness Spiritualist: L2 with 800/1800 Statline. Has 2 HOPT's. You can return a Amazoness card you control back to the Hand to special her from the Hand or GY (Limits to Amazoness Extra Deck summons for the rest of the turn). If special summoned you can search Polymerization from the Deck to Hand. She's simple yet effective in setting up Fusion plays and is yet another recurring Threat each turn. She also enables great Loop Potential. Use Amazoness Village as bounce target to summon her without loosing your Normal summon. Use her to bounce Amazoness Willpower for another usage and trigger Amazoness Village in the process. Reuse Amazoness Hall and Amazoness Hot Spring every turn or reuse the search effects of Amazoness Princess and Amazoness War Chief. This card is absolutely useful and versatile and I'm really liking her. 

Amazoness Golden Whip Master & Amazoness Silver Sword Master: L5 with 2000/1200 & L3 with 1200/2000 Statline. Pendulum Scales 1 & 7. Pendulum Zone Effects: If an attack is declared involving a Amazoness Monster Golden Whip can target and destroy any Spell Trap on the field and Silver Sword can recycle a Amazoness Spell/Trap from the GY back to the Hand (HOPT). They both give each Amazoness 100 ATK times their Level. Monster Effects: They both can be placed into the Pendulum Zone if destroyed by Battle or Card effect. If a Amazoness is Special summoned while they are in the GY they can be placed into the Pendulum Zone (Both effects are HOPTs).

They are great Fusion Materials since they end up in the Pendulum Zone after that. They can create a 5200 ATK Amazoness Augusta which then easily OTKs with her ability to attack Twice. They also create a great ressource Loop for the in Archetype Spell & Traps and can remove your own Amazoness Onslaught to trigger a revival effect during the Battle Phase. Their next advantage is the Ability to Pendulum summon all Main Deck Monsters easily onto the field and even other copies of themselves from the Extra Deck back to the field. Finally cards like Amazoness Pet Liger King can destroy them without loosing any advantage. In total these 2 Pendulum Monsters are a great help for the Amazoness Tribe. 

And that's all for the Monsters up next is the Backrow. 


Magic Moments in the Village 

Polymerization needs no explanation but Fusion Substitute may need one. It's always treated as Polymerization (Even during Deck Building) and can only use Monsters from the field but it can also banish itself from the GY to return a Fusion in your GY back to the Extra Deck and draw one card. This is easily done in this Deck and getting easy access to Draw and Recycling is a very nice option. Polymerization is still easier to use so we play 2 of them and only 1 Fusion Substitute.

Amazoness Village is a Field Spell that has already been mentioned often by now. Amazoness Monsters gain 200 ATK and once per turn when a Amazoness is destroyed by Battle or Card effect you can Special a Amazoness from Deck with an equal or lower level. Amazoness Pet Liger King and Amazoness Willpower are 2 easy ways to trigger this effect outside of the Battle Phase and Amazoness Spiritualist may then bounce it to be able to use this effect again during the Battle Phase. Certainly needs a little setup to be used optimal but it's worth the effort. 

Amazoness Call searches any Amazoness Card from the Deck or sends it to the GY (Useful for Amazoness Secret Arts) and can be banished from the GY to target an Amazoness Monster which then can attack every Monster from the opponent once but only that Monster can attack that turn. This card can only be activated once each turn but it's a quick play spell. I mentioned this card during the Monster section many times for good reasons. This Card is as essencial as Amazoness Princess.

Amazoness Secret Arts is a quick play Spell that works like Polymerization but for Amazoness Monsters only. You can banish this card from the GY to be able to send a Fusion Monster from the Extra Deck to the GY as Material if you Fusion summon this turn as a one time effect. Only one effect of Amazoness Secret Arts can be used per turn and only once that turn. Quite limited but also quite devastating this card enables quick effect fusion summons at any time and easy lines into Amazoness Augusta. It can be recycled each turn with Amazoness Silver Sword Master unlike Polymerization which can't be reused in this Deck.

Amazoness Archers is a normal Trap that can be activated when the opponent declares an attack and you control an Amazoness Monster. Force all Monsters from the opponent to attack position (Flip effects are not activated), they loose 500 ATK permanently and have to attack if possible. If you use Amazoness Secret Arts to turn a weak Monster into a big Boss after using this card it's pretty likely the opponent will OTK himself from that position. This card is quite devastating but obviously as a Battle Phase trick also limited in it's usability. Still this card can be a very unwelcome surprise for the opponent and it's pretty fun to resolve successfully. 

Amazoness Willpower is Call of the Haunted but for Amazoness Monsters and that Monster has to attack if possible and can't change it's Battle Position. Reuse this card with Amazoness Spiritualist each turn and trigger Amazoness Village in the process to really start generating advantage with this otherwise pretty normal card. 

Amazoness Onslaught used to be a centerstone of attention before the Strategy shifted to Fusion summoning but is still very strong. It's a permanent Trap that can special a Amazoness from Hand during the Battle Phase and give it a 500 ATK Boost until the End Phase. After damage calculation if an Amazoness Battled you can banish the opponents Monster. If destroyed you can revive a Amazoness from the GY. No limitations on this card and non targeting banishing are what makes this card so strong. Be sure to have it ready with Amazoness War Chief , Amazoness Princess or Amazoness Call if you need it. Destroy it with Amazoness Golden Whip Master for a reborn and then use Amazoness Silver Sword Master on a follow up attack to recycle it for next turn. You may also use Amazoness Pet Liger King to trigger a double reborn that way (One with Onslaught one with Liger King). 

Amazoness Hall is another permanent Trap which on activation can recycle a Amazoness from the GY back to Hand or from the Extra Deck into the Pendulum Zone. If the opponent specials a Monster while you control a Amazoness Monster you can target it and gain LP equal to it's current ATK. That's a HOPT. The part I already mentioned is the Loop potential with Amazoness Spiritualist but the Fact that Amazoness actually have a card that generates LP is amazing. Do you remember Amazoness Chain Master who has a nifty LP cost or the self damaging Attacks with Amazoness Call and Amazoness Princess or Amazoness Sage combined? Thanks to this card you can actually manage to survive in these moments which makes this card great to have.

Amazoness Hot Spring is the final permanent Trap that on activation searches a Amazoness from Deck to Hand or places it in the Pendulum Zone. If you take Battle Damage and you control a Amazoness Monster you can gain LP equal to the Damage you took. That's a HOPT. The 2nd piece in the Puzzle which prevents you from reaching 0 LP easily but doesn't actually generates any LP plus. Instead it has an search which once again can be reset with Amazoness Spiritualist. Amazoness Hall and Amazoness Hot Spring help out a lot in the post turn 2 survivability for the Amazoness Tribe. 

That's the Main Deck done. Onto the Extra Deck! 


Princess < Queen < Empress < Augusta

Like I said earlier the overall Amazoness Strategy shifted to Fusion summoning but are these Monsters worth it? Let's find out: 

Amazoness Augusta: L10 with 3200/2800 Statline. Needs a Amazoness Fusion Monster and any other Amazoness as Material. The opponent can't target other Amazoness cards with card effects and he also can't destroy them by card effects. If this card is Fusion summoned with Amazoness Queen or Amazoness Empress she can attack Twice. If Fusion summoned you can special a Amazoness Monster from the Deck. That's a HOPT. 

This card is the strongest Amazoness of them all and can easily OTK the opponent if at least one Pendulum Monster is active. If you summon her twice every Amazoness Card including herself is immune to targeting and destruction from the opponent, your backrow included. The cherry on top is the Fact she brings out another Amazoness from Deck if she's fusion summoned which makes her even stronger. Truly a magnificient Boss Monster and the absolute strongest Amazoness of them all. 

Amazoness Empress: L8 with 2800/2400 Statline. Needs Amazoness Queen and any other Amazoness as Material. Other Amazoness Cards can't be destroyed by Battle or Card effects. Amazoness Monsters inflict piercing damage. If this card is destroyed by Battle or leaves the field through an opponents card effect you can special a Amazoness Queen from Hand, Deck or GY. 

Second in command she has a notable difference in her protection effect. It applies to your effects too so a Amazoness Pet Liger King is unable to use his effect if he doesn't target Amazoness Empress itself. Just like Amazoness Augusta two copies of Amazoness Empress will prevent any Amazoness Card from being destroyed by Battle or Card effect, backrow included. Enabling piercing for all Amazoness Monsters makes cards like Amazoness Augusta with Amazoness Call combined even more dangerous. Her floating effect is able to summon the OG Amazoness Queen from the Deck or Amazoness Princess from Hand/GY on top of her other already strong effects. She's pretty strong especially with Amazoness Augusta combined. 

Amazoness Pet Liger King: L9 with 2900/2800 Statline. Needs a L5 or higher Amazoness and any other Amazoness as Material. The opponent can't attack another Monster. You can destroy any Amazoness Card on your field (Him included) to revive a Amazoness Warrior Monster from the GY but Amazoness Pet Liger King can't attack that turn and it's a HOPT.

He's easy to be summoned with six L5 or higher Monsters in the Main Deck and more in the Extra Deck. He can create a perfect attack Wall if you control him twice or with Amazoness Archers combined force the opponent to attack him. After all with Pendulum Setup he has 4700 ATK which is more then enough to make the opponent finish himself. The revival effect is great to trigger Amazoness Village since the "and if you do" in his card text won't make Village miss timing. Overall he has the role of both an great extender and defender.

Amazoness Pet Liger: L7 with 2500/2400 Statline. Needs Amazoness Tiger and any other Amazoness as Material. If he attacks you can make him gain 500 ATK during Damage Calculation only. If an Amazoness Monster attacked you can target an opponents Monster and permanently decrease it's ATK by 800. The opponent can't target other Amazoness Monsters for attacks. 

The difference in his attack lock is that he protects Amazoness Monsters only. 2 copies will create an attack lock which excludes Missus Radiant who's there to strengthen all your Monsters and enable more Recycling. The ATK decrease sounds weak but we even play Amazoness Blowpiper so we are in deep with this ATK decrease Strategy and he certainly helps out a lot in that regard. This can trigger multiple times at once and has no limitations so reducing opponents Monsters to 0 ATK is very possible. 

With the Boss Monsters done it's time to talk about the less nice things. 


War around the Village at it's Climax

Time for the usual Weakpoints analysis. Amazoness like every Deck is not perfect. The whole Spell & Trap removal is attack based which means a card as simple as Swords of Revealing Light can completely stop you in your Tracks. In these cases the TCG Decklist with the added Amazoness Archer instead of Amazoness Spy has a realistic way to victory left but as for this List it looks a bit dark for you then. Adding generic Extra Deck Monsters is a easy solution but don't forget the limitations which Amazoness Spiritualist and Amazoness War Chief create. 

Non targeting removal also bites this Strategy a lot since there's no protection against that even with your Bosses. Quick effect Fusion Summoning with Amazoness Secret Arts is an interesting way to deal with that problem at least a little bit.

The Final problem is banishing. Macro Cosmos and Dimension Shifter don't make playing impossible but any kind of backup Plan is done for with these cards active. 

Outside of these 3 major problems the rest looks pretty shiny and good for this Archetype. Unlike other Battle Phase oriented strategies Amazoness has plenty of options and protection available and can win in different creative ways my favourite being stealing Nibiru, the Primal Being with Amazoness Chain Master to use him on the opponent to then crash Amazoness Swords Woman into the Chonky Nibiru Token. 


Final Speech from the Queen

Amazoness is fun and unique (I noticed I often write this) but really, cards like Amazoness Chain Master and Amazoness Swords Woman which Scream Duel Monsters era make this Deck so special. If you like Fusion Monsters and Battle Phase related strategies which still have plenty of options available this Deck is made for you. 

I like Amazoness and you can actually easily go into Diamond and beyond with this Strategy. They are simple on paper but devastating in practice from my experience and that's why I appreciate them^^ 


Final Rating: 

★★★★★★★ OTK Potential

★★★★★★☆ Defensive Tools

★★☆☆☆☆☆ Control Options

★★★★☆☆☆ Removal Options

★★★★★★★ Recovery/Recycling

★★★★★★☆ Card Advantage

Overall Rating: ★★★★★☆☆  32/42★



Laws of the Empress

Like always there are certain rules you should know about which are listed down here:

Amazoness Queen: This is an permanent effect. 

Amazoness War Chief: 1. The special summon is an effect. 2. If you set a Quick play Spell you cannot activate it in the same turn. 

Amazoness Swords Woman: This is an permanent effect.

Amazoness Chain Master: 1. The opponent has to show his Hand. If there's no Monster nothing will happen after he showed his Hand. 2. The stolens Monsters original owner is still the opponent. If it's discarded or sent from the field to the GY it returns to the opponents GY. 

Amazoness Trainee: A Monster destroyed from this card never touches the GY. 

Amazoness Sage: This effect always activates mandatory even if there's no target. 

Amazoness Tiger: If for some reason both Amazoness Tiger and Amazoness Baby Tiger are on the field at the same time the last Monster which was summoned of these two is sent to the GY. 

Amazoness Blowpiper: 1. This effect is mandatory and applies even if this card leaves the field. 2. If this card leaves the field and is resummoned during the Standby Phase it's effect will trigger again. 

Amazoness Spy: The special summon of this card is an effect. 

Amazoness Princess: The 2nd effect has no limitations whatsoever. 

Amazoness Scouts: If a Monster already targets an Amazoness and you chain this effect, the effect which targets will resolve normally. 

Amazoness Baby Tiger: While you control Amazoness Tiger this card can't be summoned. 

Amazoness Spiritualist: Special summoning this card is an effect. 

Amazoness Golden Whip Master: You can target and destroy your own Spell/Traps

Amazoness Silver Sword Master: General Pendulum rules say a Pendulum Monster is placed face up in the Extra Deck if it would be send from the field to the GY. From Hand and Deck it will be sent to the GY normally. 

Fusion Substitute: This card is always treated as Polymerization even during Deck Building. 

Amazoness Village: This card can miss timing. Note that words like "and" and "and if you do" won't make this card miss timing. 

Amazoness Call: Using the GY effect twice in the same turn on the same Monster gains no benefit. 

Amazoness Secret Arts: The GY effect sends a Fusion Monster from the Extra Deck to the GY as Material. That Monster in the GY can't be revived to the field but can be returned to the Extra Deck with other recycling cards. 

Amazoness Archers: 1. The ATK decrease is permanent. 2. Only Monsters currently on the field will be forced to attack. 

Amazoness Willpower: You have to enter the Battle Phase if you control a Monster summoned with this card and you have to attack if possible. 

Amazoness Onslaught: 1. Banishing a Monster does not target. 2. You may destroy this card yourself to trigger it's last effect. 

Amazoness Hall: This card checks current ATK not original ATK. 

Amazoness Hot Spring: You gain LP after taking the Damage. 

Amazoness Augusta: She can attack twice not just Monsters but in general.

Amazoness Empress: You also can't destroy othee cards from yourself by card effects. 

Amazoness Pet Liger King: He can create a perfect attack Wall with 2 copies of him including out of archetype Monsters like Missus Radiant.

Amazoness Pet Liger: His ATK decrease is permanent. <!--/data/user/0/com.samsung.android.app.notes/files/clipdata/clipdata_bodytext_231008_234453_552.sdocx-->
